import React from 'react' import '../../App.css'; import './About.css' function About() { return (














From an early age, California native Jahn Dough

found joy and understanding within music. Born Devin Parhms,

Jahn Dough remembers vibing to music of all genres, from both west

and east coast hip hop to jazz and blues. His early hip hop influences include

Spice 1, Xzibit, MC Eiht, DJ Quik, Biggie, and E-40 to name a few. Specifically, Jahn Dough

credits his eclectic taste to the influence of his older brother, Darnell. They would listen to

hip hop from all eras while driving around in the car, windows down – it was then when Jahn Dough began rapping,

memorizing Dr. Dre’s “2001” from top to bottom. In 2007, Jahn Dough moved to Texas. Once there, he began to grow an appreciation through

for southern music in artists like OutKast, 36 Mafia, and UGK. Jahn Dough began experimenting with his own sound in early junior high writing music.

He recorded his first mix tape as a senior in high school. Throughout college, he continued writing and recording, developing and honing

his writing ability and sound. For Jahn Dough, music has always been a way to escape and release from his external

environment. He’s grown a love for the creative process and enjoys the freedom it brings him, both

with writing and experimenting with many different sounds. Jahn Dough’s relatable story- telling

and writing ability has been heavily influenced by artists like Isaiah Rashad,

Andre 3000, Kendrick Lamar and Spice 1, to name a few. His goal has

always been to be as authentic as possible, and relate to his

audience. Jahn Dough wants to share with his audience

his story and how that has influenced

how he views this world.












) } export default About
